# Cursor Rules for CampusConnect

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router), React, Tailwind CSS, TypeScript.
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Edge Functions, Auth).

## Code Style & AI Guidelines
- Always use TypeScript interfaces for database payloads.
- Use the @supabase/supabase-js v2 SDK.
- When generating SQL, ALWAYS write it as a Supabase Migration.
- Assume Row Level Security (RLS) is required for all tables.
- Do not apologize; output code blocks directly.